Below is the updated Open Blooms 13-Week Promotional Campaign Calendar starting THIS week in December 2025.

To make this immediately usable, the calendar begins Monday, December 1, 2025 and runs for 13 consecutive weeks through Sunday, March 1, 2026 — covering holiday gifting, winter occasions, Valentine’s Day (peak floral season), and early spring trends.

⸻

**Open Blooms 13-Week Promotional Campaign Calendar

(Starting December 2025 — With RFM Segmentation)**

Start Week: Monday, December 1, 2025
End Week: Sunday, March 1, 2026

⸻

SECTION 1 — Anchor Seasonal & Holiday Moments

Major Holidays Covered in This Window
	•	December Holiday Gifting (Dec 1–25)
	•	Christmas Eve (Wed, Dec 24)
	•	Christmas Day (Thu, Dec 25)
	•	New Year’s Eve (Dec 31)
	•	New Year’s Day (Jan 1)
	•	Winter Gifting Season (January)
	•	Valentine’s Day (Feb 14) — peak floral demand
	•	Late Winter “Brighten Your Space” Promotions (Late Feb / Early March)

Vertical-Specific Floral Moments
	•	Winter whites & holiday arrangements
	•	Poinsettias & seasonal plants
	•	Sympathy season (January is typically high)
	•	Valentine’s rose pre-sales
	•	Early spring bouquet pre-launch (March 2026)

⸻

SECTION 2 — 13-WEEK CALENDAR (Dec 2025 → Mar 2026)

Each week includes:
	•	Seasonal hook
	•	Campaign concept
	•	RFM segmentation notes
	•	Offer recommendations
	•	Cross-channel touchpoints

⸻

WEEK 1 — Dec 1–7, 2025

Theme: Holiday Gifting Kickoff
Campaign: “December Blooms Have Arrived”
RFM Targeting:
	•	Champions: Early access to holiday arrangements
	•	Loyal: Seasonal favorites bundle
	•	1X Buyers: Holiday gift guide for loved ones
	•	At-Risk: “We’ve missed you — here are this year’s best sellers”
Offer: Free holiday card upgrade
Channels: Email + Homepage hero + Social carousel

⸻

WEEK 2 — Dec 8–14, 2025

Theme: Holiday Delivery Reminder
Campaign: “Order Early for Guaranteed Delivery”
RFM:
	•	Champions → Upgrade to premium arrangements
	•	Loyal → Multi-recipient gifting suggestions
	•	Potential → “Send joy to someone special”
	•	At-Risk → Delivery urgency + small incentive
Offer: Free delivery on select bouquets
Channels: Email + SMS urgency

⸻

WEEK 3 — Dec 15–21, 2025

Theme: Last Week for Christmas Delivery
Campaign: “Last Call for Holiday Blooms”
RFM:
	•	Champions → “You’re first in line for last-minute exclusives”
	•	Loyal → “Don’t forget your holiday list”
	•	Potential → “Still shopping? We’ve got you”
	•	At-Risk → Final discount to win back
Offer: Same-day delivery emphasis
Channels: SMS heavy + Email reminder

⸻

WEEK 4 — Dec 22–28, 2025

Theme: Christmas Week + Post-Holiday Cheer
Campaign: “Festive Joy & After-Holiday Blooms”
RFM:
	•	Champions → Designer’s Choice luxury bouquets
	•	Loyal → “Thank you for a wonderful season”
	•	Potential → Seasonal sale
	•	Hibernating → “Warm up your home with winter blooms”
Offer: 10–15% off select holiday leftover arrangements
Channels: Email + Social UGC

⸻

WEEK 5 — Dec 29–Jan 4, 2026

